title: Flight passenger traffic
caption: Comparison between 2019 and subsequent years' 7-day rolling average flight passenger traffic within 1 January, 2020 and 22 March, 2021 outbound Austin-Bergstrom Intl, Austin, TX.
insights: Average passenger traffic before March, 2020 was 17.0% higher than that in 2019.
Following the onset of the pandemic in the city, a drastic drop in traffic was observed between mid-March and mid-April 2020 and reached as low as -96.0.
The general trend since the mid-April has been a slow but steady increase in flight passenger traffic and by 17 March, 2021 traffic was 51.0% points greater than the lowest point before mid-April.

In 2020, Periods surrounding holidays such as 4 July (Independence Day), 1 September (Labor Day), 27 November (Thanksgiving) and 25 - 31 December (Christmas and New Year) experienced local spikes in  passenger traffic but never rose to the levels that had been observed in 2019.
